<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jones &amp; Sterrer" authorityYear="2005" box="[479,591,284,309]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Bipaliidae" genus="Bipalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seriata" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="vagum">
<emphasis box="[479,591,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">B. vagum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been observed by WS feeding on snails. Again it is presumed that reproduction is by copulation and subsequent laying of egg capsules. It is possible that some asexual reproduction by fission may occur as in some other 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1323,364,390]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Bipaliidae" genus="Bipalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seriata" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1159,1267,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">Bipalium</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Winsor, L." box="[272,433,404,430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="61 - 100" refId="ref11728" refString="Winsor, L. (1983) A revision of the land planarian Bipalium kewense Mosely, 1878 (Turbellaria; Tricladida; Terricola). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 79, 61 - 100." type="journal article" year="1983">Winsor 1983</bibRefCitation>
). The species is certainly introduced to 
<collectingCountry box="[926,1038,404,430]" name="Bermuda" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Graff" authorityYear="1896" box="[1052,1173,404,430]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Bipaliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seriata" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Bipaliidae</taxonomicName>
originate in south­east Asia, 
<collectingCountry box="[458,518,444,470]" name="India" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[575,717,444,470]" name="Madagascar" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ogren, R. E. &amp; Kawakatsu, M. &amp; Froehlich, E. M." box="[732,944,444,470]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="63 - 103" refId="ref11294" refString="Ogren, R. E., Kawakatsu, M. &amp; Froehlich, E. M. (1997) Additions and corrections of the previous terrestrial planarian indices of the world (Turbellaria, Seriata, Tricladida, Terricola) Addendum IV. Geographic locus index: Bipaliidae; Rhynchodemidae (Rhynchodeminae; Microplaninae); Geoplanidae (Geoplaninae; Caenoplaninae; Pelmatoplaninae). Bulletin of Fuji Women's College, No. 35, Series II, 63 - 103." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Ogren 
<emphasis box="[815,867,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">et al</emphasis>
. 1997
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
